    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "A review of Cunaxidae (Acariformes, Trombidiformes): Histories and diagnoses of subfamilies and genera, keys to world species, and some new locality records" ;
    fabio:hasPart <https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29894>, <https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29896> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29894>
    dc:description "Figures 54, 55. Cunaxa key illustrations. 54 a-e Proterosomal shield, dorsal 54 a Proterosomal shield with oval area formed by broken striae around pt present, mps present 54 b Proterosomal shield with oval area formed by broken striae around pt absent, mps present 54 c Proterosomal shield striated, mps present 54 d Proterosomal shield smooth, mps present 54 e Proterosomal shield with lps absent 55 a Smooth f 1, h 1 55 b Spiculate f 1, h 1." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29894" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29896>
    dc:description "Figures 56 - 60. Cunaxa key illustrations. 56 a, b Integumental striations 57 a Chelicera with longitudinal striations present 57 a Chelicera with longitudinal striations absent 58 a-f Examples of variation in the hysterosomal median plate 59 a Pedipalp telofemoral apophysis uncinated 59 b Pedipalp telofemoral apophysis truncated 59 c Pedipalp telofemoral apophysis short and cone-like 59 d Pedipalp telofemoral apophysis short and finger-like 59 e Pedipalp telofemoral femoral apophysis long 60 a Pedipalp tibiotarsus with small teeth present 60 b Pedipalp tibiotarsus with small teeth absent." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29896" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

